President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Cory T. Wilson of Mississippi as Circuit Judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit. Wilson currently serves as a Judge on the Mississippi Court of Appeals and has previously served in the Mississippi House of Representatives, as well as in various roles in state government and the Department of Defense. He earned his B.B.A. from the University of Mississippi and his J.D. from Yale Law School.

Additionally, Kristi Haskins Johnson of Mississippi has been nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of Mississippi. Johnson currently serves as the Solicitor General of the State of Mississippi and has previously worked as an Assistant United States Attorney and in private practice. She earned her B.A. from the University of Mississippi and her J.D. from the Mississippi College School of Law.